<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="513" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Fox</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-13"><hi rend="italic">June 13,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Government of Ecuador having withdrawn its troops to Huigra Alausi
                            Guanote Pasaje and other points on line of railways, has been informed
                            that Peru has landed great quantity of heavy artillery at Tumbez and is
                            mounting same into position and otherwise is making strenuous
                            preparations for war. The President of Ecuador and cabinet ministers
                            deeply concerned.</p>
                        <p>I am expecting prompt action on the part of Ecuador.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>